<h2> <center> Running the Code </center> </h2>
 
In order to run our HDR algorithm without using Ward's algorithm, all you have to do is call the <i>main</i> function in the folder <i>src/hdr/</i> and pass in parameter values for the directory in which the images are located, and a lamda value for the level of smoothing.  In the directory where the images are located, there should be a file with the extension <i>.info</i> in which the first line contains the number of images, and the remaining lines contain the name of each image along with its shutter speed (<a href = "img/infoFile/museum.info"> see example here</a>).  The main function will show as well as write images using the Matlab tone mapping function, Reinhard's local tone mapping function, and Reinhard's global tone mapping function.  In order use our Ward's algorithm implementation, you must call the <i>WardMain</i> function in the folder <i>src/WardsAlg/</i> and pass in a directory where the images and <i>.info</i> file are located.  The WardMain function will write new images that have been shifted and cropped based on the output of Ward's algorithm with and without using an edge filter.  The location of these output images are <i>src/WardsAlg/Dataset/outputEdgeFilter/</i> for the edge filtered images, and <i>src/WardsAlg/Dataset/outputNoFilter/</i> for the non-filtered images.



